{"name": "mohawk", "metadata": {"name": "mohawk", "version": "1.1.0", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP"], "home_page": "https://github.com/kumar303/mohawk", "license": "MPL 2.0 (Mozilla Public License)", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["six"], "summary": "Library for Hawk HTTP authorization", "upload_time": 1572275730}, "documentation": ["\nHawk lets two parties securely communicate with each other using\nmessages signed by a shared key.\nIt is based on HTTP MAC access authentication (which\nwas based on parts of OAuth 1.0).\n\nThe Mohawk API is a little different from that of the Node library\n(i.e. https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk).\nIt was redesigned to be more intuitive to developers, less prone to security problems, and more Pythonic.\n\nRead more: https://github.com/kumar303/mohawk/\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mohawk.receiver", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "mohawk.receiver.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "mohawk.receiver.Receiver", "bases": ["HawkAuthority"], "methods": [{"name": "mohawk.receiver.Receiver.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "credentials_map", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request_header", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "method", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "content_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "seen_nonce", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "localtime_offset_in_seconds", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "accept_untrusted_content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "timestamp_skew_in_seconds", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**auth_kw", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.receiver.Receiver.respond", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "content_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "always_hash_content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ext", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Respond to the request.\n\nThis generates the {attr}`mohawk.Receiver.response_header`\nattribute.\n\n```\nparam content=EmptyValue\n\nByte string of response body that will be sent.\n\ntype content=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam content_type=EmptyValue\n\ncontent-type header value for response.\n\ntype content_type=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam always_hash_content=True\n\nWhen True, content and content_type must be provided.\nRead  to learn more.\n\ntype always_hash_content=True\n\nbool\n\nparam ext=None\n\nAn external Hawk string. If not None, this value will be\nsigned so that the sender can trust it.\n\ntype ext=None\n\nstr\n```\n\n[hawk]: https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "mohawk.receiver.Receiver.response_header", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A Hawk authority that will receive and respond to requests.\n\n```\nparam credentials_map\n\nCallable to look up the credentials dict by sender ID.\nThe credentials dict must have the keys:\nid, key, and algorithm.\nSee  for an example.\n\ntype credentials_map\n\ncallable\n\nparam request_header\n\nA Hawk Authorization header\nsuch as one created by .\n\ntype request_header\n\nstr\n\nparam url\n\nAbsolute URL of the request.\n\ntype url\n\nstr\n\nparam method\n\nMethod of the request. E.G. POST, GET\n\ntype method\n\nstr\n\nparam content=EmptyValue\n\nByte string of request body.\n\ntype content=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam content_type=EmptyValue\n\ncontent-type header value for request.\n\ntype content_type=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam accept_untrusted_content=False\n\nWhen True, allow requests that do not hash their content.\nRead  to learn more.\n\ntype accept_untrusted_content=False\n\nbool\n\nparam localtime_offset_in_seconds=0\n\nSeconds to add to local time in case it's out of sync.\n\ntype localtime_offset_in_seconds=0\n\nfloat\n\nparam timestamp_skew_in_seconds=60\n\nMax seconds until a message expires. Upon expiry,\n is raised.\n\ntype timestamp_skew_in_seconds=60\n\nfloat\n```\n\n[hawk]: https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "mohawk.receiver.Receiver", "xref": {"fqname": "mohawk.receiver.Receiver", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "mohawk", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mohawk.bewit", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mohawk.bewit.get_bewit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "resource", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a bewit identifier for the resource as a string.\n\n```\nparam resource\n\nResource to generate a bewit for\n\ntype resource\n\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.bewit.parse_bewit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "bewit", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a `bewittuple` representing the parts of an encoded bewit string.\nThis has the following named attributes:\n\n> (id, expiration, mac, ext)\n\n```\nparam bewit\n\nA base64 encoded bewit string\n\ntype bewit\n\nstr\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.bewit.strip_bewit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Strips the bewit parameter out of a url.\n\nReturns (encoded_bewit, stripped_url)\n\nRaises InvalidBewit if no bewit found.\n\n```\nparam url\n\nThe url containing a bewit parameter\n\ntype url\n\nstr\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.bewit.check_bewit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "credential_lookup", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "now", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Validates the given bewit.\n\nReturns True if the resource has a valid bewit parameter attached,\nor raises a subclass of HawkFail otherwise.\n\n```\nparam credential_lookup\n\nCallable to look up the credentials dict by sender ID.\nThe credentials dict must have the keys:\nid, key, and algorithm.\nSee  for an example.\n\ntype credential_lookup\n\ncallable\n\nparam now=None\n\nUnix epoch time for the current time to determine if bewit has expired.\nIf None, then the current time as given by utc_now() is used.\n\ntype now=None\n\ninteger\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "mohawk.bewit.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.bewit.bewittuple", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mohawk.sender", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "mohawk.sender.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "mohawk.sender.Sender", "bases": ["HawkAuthority"], "methods": [{"name": "mohawk.sender.Sender.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "credentials", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "method", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "content_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "always_hash_content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "nonce", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ext", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "app", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dlg", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "seen_nonce", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "_timestamp", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.sender.Sender.accept_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "response_header", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "content_type", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "accept_untrusted_content", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "localtime_offset_in_seconds", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "timestamp_skew_in_seconds", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**auth_kw", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Accept a response to this request.\n\n```\nparam response_header\n\nA Hawk Server-Authorization header\nsuch as one created by .\n\ntype response_header\n\nstr\n\nparam content=EmptyValue\n\nByte string of the response body received.\n\ntype content=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam content_type=EmptyValue\n\nContent-Type header value of the response received.\n\ntype content_type=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam accept_untrusted_content=False\n\nWhen True, allow responses that do not hash their content.\nRead  to learn more.\n\ntype accept_untrusted_content=False\n\nbool\n\nparam localtime_offset_in_seconds=0\n\nSeconds to add to local time in case it's out of sync.\n\ntype localtime_offset_in_seconds=0\n\nfloat\n\nparam timestamp_skew_in_seconds=60\n\nMax seconds until a message expires. Upon expiry,\n is raised.\n\ntype timestamp_skew_in_seconds=60\n\nfloat\n```\n\n[hawk]: https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.sender.Sender.reconfigure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "credentials", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "mohawk.sender.Sender.request_header", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A Hawk authority that will emit requests and verify responses.\n\n```\nparam credentials\n\nDict of credentials with keys id, key,\nand algorithm. See  for an example.\n\ntype credentials\n\ndict\n\nparam url\n\nAbsolute URL of the request.\n\ntype url\n\nstr\n\nparam method\n\nMethod of the request. E.G. POST, GET\n\ntype method\n\nstr\n\nparam content=EmptyValue\n\nByte string of request body or a file-like object.\n\ntype content=EmptyValue\n\nstr or file-like object\n\nparam content_type=EmptyValue\n\ncontent-type header value for request.\n\ntype content_type=EmptyValue\n\nstr\n\nparam always_hash_content=True\n\nWhen True, content and content_type must be provided.\nRead  to learn more.\n\ntype always_hash_content=True\n\nbool\n\nparam nonce=None\n\nA string that when coupled with the timestamp will\nuniquely identify this request to prevent replays.\nIf None, a nonce will be generated for you.\n\ntype nonce=None\n\nstr\n\nparam ext=None\n\nAn external Hawk string. If not None, this value will be signed\nso that the receiver can trust it.\n\ntype ext=None\n\nstr\n\nparam app=None\n\nA Hawk application string. If not None, this value will be signed\nso that the receiver can trust it.\n\ntype app=None\n\nstr\n\nparam dlg=None\n\nA Hawk delegation string. If not None, this value will be signed\nso that the receiver can trust it.\n\ntype dlg=None\n\nstr\n\nparam seen_nonce=None\n\nA callable that returns True if a nonce has been seen.\nSee  for details.\n\ntype seen_nonce=None\n\ncallable\n```\n\n[hawk]: https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "mohawk.sender.Sender", "xref": {"fqname": "mohawk.sender.Sender", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "mohawk.util", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mohawk.util.validate_credentials", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "creds", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.random_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "length", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Generates a random string for a given length."]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.calculate_payload_hash", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "payload", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "algorithm", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content_type", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "block_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calculates a hash for a given payload."]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.calculate_mac", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mac_type", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resource", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content_hash", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calculates a message authorization code (MAC)."]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.calculate_ts_mac", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ts", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "credentials", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Calculates a message authorization code (MAC) for a timestamp."]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.normalize_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mac_type", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "resource", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "content_hash", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serializes mac_type and resource into a HAWK string."]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.parse_content_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "content_type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Cleans up content_type."]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.parse_authorization_header", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "auth_header", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Example Authorization header:\n\n    'Hawk id=\"dh37fgj492je\", ts=\"1367076201\", nonce=\"NPHgnG\", ext=\"and\n    welcome!\", mac=\"CeWHy4d9kbLGhDlkyw2Nh3PJ7SDOdZDa267KH4ZaNMY=\"'"]}, {"name": "mohawk.util.strings_match", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.utc_now", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "offset_in_seconds", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.validate_header_attr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.prepare_header_val", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.normalize_header_attr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "mohawk.util.HAWK_VER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.HAWK_HEADER_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.MAX_LENGTH", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util.allowable_header_keys", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.util._header_attribute_chars", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mohawk.exc", "documentation": ["If you want to catch any exception that might be raised,\ncatch {class}`mohawk.exc.HawkFail`.\n\n:::{important}\nNever expose an exception message publicly, say, in an HTTP\nresponse, as it may provide hints to an attacker.\n:::\n"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "mohawk.exc.HawkFail", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["All Mohawk exceptions derive from this base."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.MissingAuthorization", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["No authorization header was sent by the client."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.InvalidCredentials", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The specified Hawk credentials are invalid.\n\nFor example, the dict could be formatted incorrectly."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.CredentialsLookupError", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A {class}`mohawk.Receiver` could not look up the\ncredentials for an incoming request.\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.BadHeaderValue", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["There was an error with an attribute or value when parsing\nor creating a Hawk header."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.MacMismatch", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The locally calculated MAC did not match the MAC that was sent."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.MisComputedContentHash", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The signature of the content did not match the actual content."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.TokenExpired", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [{"name": "mohawk.exc.TokenExpired.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kw", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "mohawk.exc.TokenExpired.localtime_in_seconds", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.TokenExpired.www_authenticate", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The timestamp on a message received has expired.\n\nYou may also receive this message if your server clock is out of sync.\nConsider synchronizing it with something like [TLSdate].\n\nIf you are unable to synchronize your clock universally,\nThe [Hawk] spec mentions how you can [adjust]\nyour sender's time to match that of the receiver in the case\nof unexpected expiration.\n\nThe `www_authenticate` attribute of this exception is a header\nthat can be returned to the client. If the value is not None, it\nwill include a timestamp HMAC'd with the sender's credentials.\nThis will allow the client\nto verify the value and safely apply an offset.\n\n[adjust]: https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk#future-time-manipulation\n[hawk]: https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk\n[tlsdate]: http://linux-audit.com/tlsdate-the-secure-alternative-for-ntpd-ntpdate-and-rdate/\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.AlreadyProcessed", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The message has already been processed and cannot be re-processed.\n\nSee {ref}`nonce` for details.\n"]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.InvalidBewit", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The bewit is invalid; e.g. it doesn't contain the right number of\nparameters."]}, {"name": "mohawk.exc.MissingContent", "bases": ["HawkFail"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A payload's `content` or `content_type` were not provided.\n\nSee {ref}`skipping-content-checks` for details.\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "mohawk.base", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "mohawk.base.default_ts_skew_in_s